Current MonoGame 3D always produces a 480 x 800 back buffer. To fix this, you need to modify AndroidGameWindow.cs and add the following at line 148 (include my comments to track the change):

```
            //
            // [JWA] TotallyEvil Entertainment
            // Must set the back buffer to the client bounds, otherwise the default is always used (480 x 800)
            // 6.18.2012
            //
            _game.GraphicsDevice.PresentationParameters.BackBufferHeight = clientBounds.Height;
            _game.GraphicsDevice.PresentationParameters.BackBufferWidth = clientBounds.Width;
```

This works. I tested on an ACER Iconia and it correctly scales everything.
